# Refactor Maps.tsx into Smaller Reusable Components

Decompose [Maps.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx) (848 lines) into focused, reusable components under `admin-web/src/components/maps/`. Special emphasis on making the drag-and-drop card deck builder generic and reusable.

## Proposed Changes

### Utility Functions

#### [NEW] [mapUtils.ts](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/mapUtils.ts)

Extract all pure utility functions from [Maps.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx):
- [getRatioInputColorClass(value)](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#52-65) — color class for ratio inputs
- [sumTypeRatios(tr)](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#66-70) — sum all type ratio values
- [getFreeRatio(tr)](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#71-75) — calculate remaining free ratio
- [getFormTypeRatios(tr)](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#76-88) — normalize type ratios with defaults
- [getCardImageUrl(card)](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#89-95) — build card image URL
- Constants: `TYPE_RATIO_KEYS`, `TYPE_RATIO_ICONS`, `MAP_STATUSES`, `DEFAULT_TYPE_RATIOS`

---

### Reusable Drag-and-Drop Components

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These components are designed to be **reusable** beyond Maps — any feature that needs "pick items from a source list and drop into a target zone" can use them.

#### [NEW] [DraggableCardThumbnail.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/DraggableCardThumbnail.tsx)

A single draggable card thumbnail for the source list panel.

**Props:**
- `card: AdventureCard` — the card data
- `getImageUrl: (card) => string` — image URL resolver (default: [getCardImageUrl](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx#89-95))

Renders the card with `draggable` attribute, sets `cardId` on `dataTransfer` during `onDragStart`.

#### [NEW] [DeckDropZone.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/DeckDropZone.tsx)

The drop target area showing selected cards with remove-on-click.

**Props:**
- `cardIds: string[]` — current deck card IDs
- `allCards: AdventureCard[]` — all available cards (for lookup by ID)
- `onAdd: (cardId: string) => void` — called when a card is dropped
- `onRemove: (index: number) => void` — called when clicking remove button
- `getImageUrl?: (card) => string` — optional image URL resolver
- `emptyMessage?: string` — placeholder when deck is empty

Handles `onDragOver`, `onDragLeave`, `onDrop` with visual feedback (highlight border on drag over).

#### [NEW] [CardDeckBuilder.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/CardDeckBuilder.tsx)

Combines `DeckDropZone` + source list of `DraggableCardThumbnail` in a two-column layout.

**Props:**
- `cardIds: string[]` — selected card IDs
- `availableCards: AdventureCard[]` — all cards to choose from
- `onDeckChange: (newCardIds: string[]) => void` — callback when deck changes
- `getImageUrl?: (card) => string`
- `deckLabel?: string` — label for deck section (default: "Deck")
- `sourceLabel?: string` — label for source list (default: "Thẻ có sẵn")

This is the **main reusable component** for drag-and-drop card selection.

---

### Map-Specific Components

#### [NEW] [TypeRatioEditor.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/TypeRatioEditor.tsx)

The type ratio editor section with icon inputs and free ratio display.

**Props:**
- `typeRatios: MapTypeRatios`
- `onChange: (key: keyof MapTypeRatios, value: number) => void`

Manages its own tooltip state internally. Shows validation message when free ratio ≠ 0.

#### [NEW] [MapCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/MapCard.tsx)

Renders a single map in the list view (the card element in the grid).

**Props:**
- `map: MapType`
- `onEdit: (map: MapType) => void`

#### [NEW] [MapFormModal.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/maps/MapFormModal.tsx)

The full create/edit modal with form fields, using `CardDeckBuilder` and `TypeRatioEditor` internally. Also manages i18n editing using existing [I18nEditorPanel](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/components/i18n/I18nEditorPanel.tsx#21-99).

**Props:**
- `open: boolean`
- `editingMap: MapType | null`
- `adventureCards: AdventureCard[]`
- `onClose: () => void`
- `onSaved: () => void` — called after successful save to trigger refresh

Contains all form state, submit/delete handlers, and i18n logic internally.

---

### Page Component

#### [MODIFY] [Maps.tsx](file:///c:/Users/inter/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/TeyvatCardGameBackend/admin-web/src/pages/Maps.tsx)

Simplified to ~80 lines. Responsibilities:
- Fetch maps and adventure cards
- Render loading skeleton
- Render `PageHeader` + list of `MapCard`
- Manage modal open/close state
- Render `MapFormModal`

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run TypeScript compiler: `cd admin-web && npx tsc --noEmit`
- Run Vite production build: `cd admin-web && npx vite build`

Both commands must complete with zero errors.
